<div class="box1">
    <img src="static/WSN" style="width:432px; height: 300px;float:right;">
    <h1 style="text-decoration:underline; text-align: initial; font-style: italic;">Wireless sensing system</h1>
    <p style="text-indent:0px; font-size: 20px;">SHM systems were built with wired sensor networks, but the great reliability and 
        low installation and maintenance costs of WSNs have made them a promising alternative platform.
        The huge cost savings from deploying WSNs for SHM would allow them to be used in critical public 
        and private infrastructure, increasing the adoption of applications 
        such as short-term structural monitoring. Such systems increase the lifespan of many facilities 
        by detecting problems early, reduce the cost of routine inspections, and, most importantly, 
        improve public safety.</p></div>

<div class="box2">
    <img src="static/Rpi.jpg" style="width:432px; height: 300px;float:left;">
    <h1 style="text-decoration:underline; text-align: initial; font-style: italic;text-align: right;">Raspberry pi</h1>
    <p style="text-indent:0px; font-size: 20px;text-align: right;">The raspberry pi does the necessary computations to determine the SHM status, 
        including determining the position and extent of any damage. 
        The Raspberry Pi serves as a hub for data collection from several NRF transceivers positioned 
        throughout the building. Using a Wi-Fi module, the Raspberry Pi will transfer the data to the cloud.
        The data will be saved in the cloud and accessible from any mobile device. 
        The technology has been validated in the lab using a real test bed.</p></div>
</div>

<div class="box3">
    <img src="static/cloud.jpg" style="width:432px; height: 300px;float:right;">
    <h1 style="text-decoration:underline; text-align: initial; font-style: italic;">Cloud database</h1>
    <p style="text-indent:0px; font-size: 20px;">Acceleration at a sampling rate of 100-500 Hz is the principal data source for SHM. 
        This sample rate generates significant amounts of data, especially when numerous sensors 
        are recorded on a structure. 
        A cloud-SHM data sharing website was created to enable data synchronisation between smartphone 
        and website, as well as data uploading and sharing, which can improve monitoring and 
        big data integration efficiency, as well as the possibility of big data collection and 
        quick structural safety evaluation.</p></div>
</div>

